domain_model.plantuml:
@startuml
class Facility {
  +ambient_temperature_range: String
  +roof_load_capacity: String
  +operating_hours: String
  +wifi_speed: String
  +notification_time: String
  +food_storage_capacity: String
  +bed_count: Integer
  +mobile_cot_count: Integer
  +shower_count: Integer
  +toilet_count: Integer
  +sink_count: Integer
  +exercise_space: String
  +eating_space: String
  +ice_core_capacity: Integer
  +ice_core_temperature_range: String
  +implement_disposal_system(): void
  +process_waste(): void
  +store_ice_cores(): void
  +monitor_energy_consumption(): void
  +generate_daily_report(): void
  +conserve_energy(): void
  +store_fuel(): void
  +withstand_temperatures(): void
  +generate_potable_water(): void
  +operate(): void
  +notify_occupants(failure_type: String): void
  +test_power_generation_subsystem(): void
  +test_heating_equipment(): void
  +test_water_filtration_equipment(): void
}

class WaterRecyclingSubsystem {
  +safety_water_standards: String
  +filter_water(): void
}

class WaterStorageSubsystem {
  +water_types: String
  +capacity_requirements: String
  +store_water(): void
}

class MonitoringDevice {
  +water_quality: String
  +contamination_levels: String
  +alert_lsf(maintenance_required: Boolean): void
  +communicate_water_quality(): void
  +communicate_contamination_levels(): void
}

class Network {
  +download_speed: String
  +upload_speed: String
  +support_download_speed(): void
  +support_upload_speed(): void
}

class ControlSystem {
  +password_protection: Boolean
  +operate_via_smart_device(): void
  +operate_via_control_panel(): void
}

class Crew {
  +monitor_control_system(): void
  +control_facility(): void
}

class RefrigerationSystem {
  +refrigeration_space: String
  +provide_refrigeration_space(): void
}

class FreezerSystem {
  +freezer_space: String
  +provide_freezer_space(): void
}

class PotableWaterSystem {
  +ph_level: String
  +feature_visible_display(): void
}

class ResearchTeam {
  +establish_cloud_storage(): void
  +interface_with_windows_pc(): void
  +interface_with_radio_system(): void
}

class FacilityDatabase {
  +access_files(): void
  +identify_files(): void
}

class DedicatedApplication {
  +retrieve_data(): void
}

WaterRecyclingSubsystem *-- MonitoringDevice
WaterStorageSubsystem *-- MonitoringDevice
MonitoringDevice --> Facility
Crew --> ControlSystem
Crew --> Facility
DedicatedApplication --> MonitoringDevice
@enduml

missing_requirements.description: Ice core identification, labeling, and tracking system missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall provide a system to uniquely identify, label, and track each of the 20 ice cores with metadata including collection date, location coordinates, depth, and storage location within the facility.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-011 specifies storage of 20 ice cores, but the domain model method store_ice_cores and the requirements lack any provisions for scientific tracking and identification, which is essential for research integrity.

missing_requirements.description: Maximum crew capacity and occupancy limits not defined
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall accommodate a maximum of 6 occupants simultaneously, with clear occupancy limits defined for safety and resource allocation purposes.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-021 specifies 'at least five beds' and REQ-032 mentions 'five chairs', but no maximum capacity is defined. The Crew class exists in the domain model but lacks capacity constraints critical for life support calculations.

missing_requirements.description: Emergency power system and backup power requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include an emergency backup power system capable of maintaining critical life support functions (heating, water filtration, communications) for a minimum of 72 hours during primary power system failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-068 tests power generation every 8 hours and REQ-014 mentions radio battery backup, but no comprehensive emergency power requirements exist for life support in extreme Antarctic conditions.

missing_requirements.description: Air quality management and ventilation system requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include an air filtration and ventilation system that maintains CO2 levels below 1000 ppm, provides fresh air circulation of at least 20 CFM per occupant, and includes air quality monitoring with alerts for dangerous gas concentrations.
missing_requirements.rationale: This is a sealed life support facility operating 24/7 (REQ-060) in extreme conditions, but no air quality or ventilation requirements exist despite being critical for crew health and safety.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall process waste through segregation of organic, inorganic, and hazardous materials with compaction ratios of at least 4:1 for organic waste and secure containment for hazardous materials until removal.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes process_waste method and REQ-006 covers disposal system implementation, but no specific requirements exist for the actual waste processing procedures.

missing_requirements.description: Data backup and recovery procedures not defined
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall automatically backup all scientific data and system logs to both local redundant storage and cloud storage daily, with recovery procedures capable of restoring data within 4 hours of system failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-017 establishes cloud storage and REQ-048 covers database access, but critical scientific data backup and recovery procedures are missing for this remote research facility.

missing_requirements.description: Monitoring device calibration and accuracy requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All monitoring devices shall maintain accuracy within ±2% of measured values and shall be calibrated monthly using certified reference standards, with calibration records maintained in the facility database.
missing_requirements.rationale: Multiple monitoring devices exist in the domain model with critical measurement functions (REQ-003, REQ-005), but no accuracy or calibration requirements ensure measurement reliability.

missing_requirements.description: System response time performance requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The control system shall respond to user commands within 3 seconds for routine operations and database queries shall complete within 5 seconds under normal operating conditions.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-084, REQ-085 specify crew control capabilities and REQ-048 covers database operations, but no performance requirements exist beyond 1-minute failure notifications.

missing_requirements.description: Equipment storage access control and procedures not specified
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The drilling equipment storage unit shall implement role-based access control with audit logging, requiring supervisor authorization for heavy machinery access and maintaining equipment checkout/checkin procedures.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-010 specifies storage for drilling equipment and REQ-081 mentions replacement hardware storage, but no access control or procedures are defined for valuable and potentially dangerous equipment.

missing_requirements.description: Subsystem integration and coordination requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall coordinate resource allocation between subsystems, prioritizing life support functions over non-critical operations during resource constraints, with automated load balancing for power and water systems.
missing_requirements.rationale: Multiple subsystems exist in the domain model with potential resource conflicts, but no integration requirements exist for coordinated operation in the resource-constrained Antarctic environment.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with EPA Safe Drinking Water Act standards and WHO guidelines for drinking water quality. Acceptance criteria: Water output shall meet or exceed EPA Primary Drinking Water Standards (40 CFR 141) with testing verification every 24 hours. Water filtration efficiency shall be ≥99.9% for bacteria and ≥99.99% for viruses.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is too vague about which specific standards apply and lacks testable acceptance criteria for verifying compliance with safety standards.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that automatically alerts facility occupants within 5 minutes when filter replacement is needed (based on flow rate degradation >20% or pressure differential >15 PSI) or maintenance is required. Alerts shall be delivered via visual display, audible alarm, and mobile application notifications. Data retrieval shall occur via dedicated application with real-time monitoring capabilities.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific criteria for when alerts are triggered, alert delivery methods, and performance requirements for the monitoring system.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for up to 6 occupants for 30 days, meeting minimum capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS document version 2.1. Acceptance criteria: Potable water storage ≥500 gallons, gray water storage ≥200 gallons, black water storage ≥150 gallons, with appropriate separation and containment systems.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement references an external document without specifying version or providing backup capacity requirements, making it difficult to verify compliance independently.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that continuously measures and communicates water quality parameters (pH, turbidity, chlorine residual, bacterial count) and contamination levels to the LSF control system every 15 minutes. Acceptance criteria: pH monitoring accuracy ±0.1, turbidity measurement range 0-100 NTU with ±2% accuracy, automatic alerts when parameters exceed safe thresholds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific water quality parameters to monitor, communication frequency, measurement accuracy requirements, and alert thresholds.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Process waste. The facility shall implement a disposal system for trash and waste that remains effective under extreme weather conditions.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall implement a waste disposal system capable of processing solid waste, organic waste, and recyclables that operates effectively in ambient temperatures from -40°F to 80°F with wind speeds up to 100 mph. Acceptance criteria: System shall process minimum 50 lbs of waste per day, maintain sealed containment during extreme weather, and comply with Antarctic Treaty waste management protocols.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement is vague about what constitutes 'extreme weather conditions' and lacks specific performance criteria for waste processing capacity and effectiveness measures.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide storage for non-perishable food items in a clean, dry environment (humidity <60%, temperature 32°F-70°F) within 10 feet of the kitchen area, and refrigerated/frozen storage for perishable goods for minimum 30-day supply. Acceptance criteria: Non-perishable storage ≥100 cubic feet with pest-proof containers, refrigerated storage at 32-40°F, frozen storage at 0°F to -10°F.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific environmental conditions, proximity requirements, storage duration, capacity requirements, and temperature specifications for different storage types.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall monitor the operational health of critical equipment via a network of wired and wireless sensors with 99.5% uptime, covering power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling systems. Acceptance criteria: Sensors shall report status every 60 seconds, detect failures within 30 seconds, provide predictive maintenance alerts 48 hours before anticipated failure, and maintain communication range of 500 feet.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific monitoring frequency, failure detection timeframes, sensor performance requirements, and network reliability specifications.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Provide sufficient storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with appropriate environmental controls.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide minimum 2000 square feet of storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery up to 10,000 lbs, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with environmental controls maintaining temperature 40-70°F and humidity <50%. Acceptance criteria: Floor load capacity ≥250 lbs/sq ft, overhead clearance ≥12 feet, vehicle access doors minimum 12x10 feet.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific space requirements, weight capacity, environmental control specifications, and access requirements for different types of equipment.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store ice cores. The facility shall be capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice cores at temperatures maintained between $-40^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$ and $20^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide freezer storage capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice core samples (each up to 3 feet long, 4 inches diameter) at temperatures maintained between -40°F and 20°F with ±2°F accuracy. Acceptance criteria: Temperature monitoring every 15 minutes, automated alerts for temperature excursions, backup power for 48 hours minimum, individual storage tubes with identification tracking.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing ice core size specifications, temperature accuracy requirements, monitoring frequency, and backup power requirements for critical storage.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall support bidirectional scientific data exchange with the US research laboratory through AES-256 encrypted transmission over satellite internet connection. Acceptance criteria: Data transfer rates ≥1 Mbps upload/download, encryption key rotation every 30 days, automatic retry for failed transmissions, data integrity verification using checksums, 99.9% successful transmission rate.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific encryption standards, data transfer performance requirements, reliability metrics, and data integrity verification methods.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least one radio for communication with McMurdo Station, which must operate on battery backup, feature a hand-crank function, and utilize solar power.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The LSF shall contain at least one HF/VHF radio capable of communicating with McMurdo Station over 500-mile range, operating on battery backup for minimum 72 hours, featuring hand-crank charging capability (5 minutes cranking = 30 minutes operation), and 50W solar panel charging system. Acceptance criteria: Clear voice communication in 90% weather conditions, automatic antenna tuning, emergency frequency monitoring.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing communication range requirements, battery backup duration, charging performance specifications, and communication quality standards.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least one camera for video conferencing.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The LSF shall contain at least one HD camera (minimum 1080p resolution) for video conferencing with pan/tilt/zoom capabilities, supporting standard protocols (H.264, SIP, WebRTC). Acceptance criteria: 30 fps video capture, automatic low-light adjustment, 180-degree viewing angle, compatible with major conferencing platforms (Zoom, Teams, WebEx), integrated microphone with noise cancellation.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing camera specifications, video quality requirements, compatibility standards, and audio capabilities for effective video conferencing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least three computers to support data transmission, with data storage maintained on an encrypted server.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The LSF shall contain at least three computers (minimum Intel i5 or equivalent, 16GB RAM, 1TB SSD) to support scientific data transmission and facility operations, with data storage maintained on an AES-256 encrypted server with minimum 10TB capacity. Acceptance criteria: RAID 5 configuration for redundancy, automated daily backups, 99.9% uptime, role-based access control, audit logging.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing computer specifications, server capacity requirements, redundancy measures, backup procedures, and access control mechanisms.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The US-based Research Team shall establish cloud-based storage accessible by the facility via the World Wide Web.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The US-based Research Team shall establish secure cloud-based storage (minimum 50TB capacity) accessible by the facility via encrypted HTTPS connection over the World Wide Web. Acceptance criteria: 99.99% availability SLA, AES-256 encryption at rest and in transit, multi-factor authentication, automated backup with 30-day retention, bandwidth throttling capabilities, API access for automated data uploads.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing storage capacity requirements, security specifications, availability guarantees, authentication methods, and access control mechanisms.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The Research Team shall interface directly with a dedicated Windows PC and the radio system.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The Research Team shall interface directly with a dedicated Windows PC (Windows 10 Pro or later) via secure remote desktop connection and the radio system via digital radio modem interface. Acceptance criteria: Secure VPN connection with certificate-based authentication, remote desktop session encryption, radio interface supporting PSK31/FT8 digital modes, automated connection retry, session logging for audit purposes.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific interface methods, security requirements, connection protocols, and technical specifications for both PC and radio interfaces.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall be designed for transportability by LC-130 or C-130 Hercules aircraft to McMurdo Station.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The LSF shall be designed as modular components for transportability by LC-130 or C-130 Hercules aircraft to McMurdo Station. Acceptance criteria: Maximum module dimensions 8'W x 8'H x 16'L, maximum module weight 15,000 lbs, tie-down points rated for 9G loading, environmental sealing for -65°F transport temperatures, complete assembly possible within 72 hours using standard tools.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific dimensional and weight constraints, structural requirements for air transport, environmental protection needs, and assembly time requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall also be designed for transport by helicopter, truck, or sleds pulled by ground vehicles.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The LSF shall be designed for transport by helicopter (maximum 8,000 lb external load), truck (maximum 80,000 lb gross vehicle weight), or sleds pulled by tracked vehicles (maximum 12,000 lb loads). Acceptance criteria: Helicopter lift points rated for 3:1 safety factor, truck transport without special permits, sled skis with 40 PSI ground pressure rating, modular breakdown for weight distribution.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific weight limits for different transport modes, structural requirements for lifting points, and ground pressure specifications for snow/ice travel.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Provide accommodation with at least five beds and one mobile cot.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide sleeping accommodation with at least five fixed beds (standard single size 36"x80") and one mobile cot (minimum 30"x72") with appropriate bedding storage. Acceptance criteria: Beds rated for 300 lb capacity, individual privacy curtains or partitions, bedside storage for personal items (minimum 2 cubic feet per bed), adequate ventilation and lighting for each sleeping area.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing bed specifications, privacy requirements, storage needs, and environmental conditions for sleeping areas.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least one shower.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall include at least one shower with temperature-controlled water supply (85-110°F), minimum 36"x36" shower area, waterproof enclosure, and adequate drainage. Acceptance criteria: Water flow rate 2.5 GPM minimum, instant hot water availability, slip-resistant flooring, ventilation fan rated for 100% humidity, privacy lock mechanism.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing water temperature control, space dimensions, safety features, drainage requirements, and privacy specifications.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least one toilet.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall include at least one flush toilet connected to the black water system with adequate privacy enclosure and ventilation. Acceptance criteria: Standard height toilet (15-17 inches), 1.6 gallon per flush maximum, privacy door with lock, exhaust fan rated for 50 CFM, toilet paper holder, hand sanitizer dispenser, adequate lighting (minimum 30 foot-candles).
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing toilet specifications, privacy requirements, ventilation standards, and associated fixtures and lighting requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall have at least two sinks.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall have at least two sinks with hot and cold running water, one in the bathroom area and one in the kitchen/food preparation area. Acceptance criteria: Kitchen sink minimum 22"x25" double bowl, bathroom sink minimum 19"x17", water temperature 85-110°F, hands-free operation (sensor or foot pedal), soap dispensers, paper towel dispensers, adequate task lighting.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing sink specifications, location requirements, water temperature control, hygiene features, and lighting requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall provide laundry capability.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide complete laundry capability including washing, drying, and folding area with appropriate water supply, drainage, and ventilation. Acceptance criteria: Hot water supply (120-140°F), 220V electrical supply, adequate drainage for 40 gallons, ventilation for moisture removal, detergent storage, folding surface minimum 6 square feet, clothes hanging area.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific capability requirements, utility needs, space requirements, and associated infrastructure for complete laundry operations.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least one washing machine.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall include at least one washing machine with minimum 3.5 cubic foot capacity, multiple wash cycles, and water/energy efficient operation. Acceptance criteria: ENERGY STAR certified, cold water washing capability, 220V power requirement, water usage <25 gallons per load, vibration isolation mounting, lint filter, automatic shutoff for unbalanced loads.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing machine specifications, capacity requirements, efficiency standards, installation requirements, and safety features.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least one drying machine.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall include at least one clothes drying machine with minimum 3.5 cubic foot capacity, multiple heat settings, and proper ventilation to exterior. Acceptance criteria: Electric or gas operation, moisture sensing auto-shutoff, lint filter system, exterior venting with damper, timer and temperature controls, maximum 75 dB operation noise level.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing machine specifications, ventilation requirements, noise levels, safety features, and energy source options.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall be equipped with at least one first aid kit.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall be equipped with at least one comprehensive first aid kit compliant with OSHA standards (29 CFR 1910.266) for remote locations, stored in clearly marked, easily accessible location. Acceptance criteria: ANSI Class A or B first aid kit, supplies for 6 persons for 30 days, temperature-controlled storage (40-80°F), expiration date tracking, inventory checklist, wall-mounted cabinet with clear labeling.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing regulatory compliance standards, kit specifications, storage requirements, inventory management, and accessibility requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall have at least one set of AED defibrillators compliant with 29 CFR 1915.87 (OSHA Maritime).
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall have at least one AED (Automated External Defibrillator) unit compliant with 29 CFR 1915.87 (OSHA Maritime) and FDA approved. Acceptance criteria: Adult and pediatric capabilities, voice prompts in English, battery life minimum 4 years standby, self-testing capability, storage temperature range -4°F to 122°F, wall-mounted cabinet with alarm, training materials included, monthly inspection log.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific AED capabilities, FDA approval requirements, environmental operating ranges, maintenance procedures, and training requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall provide a minimum of 100 square feet of space for physical exercise.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide a minimum of 100 square feet of clear floor space for physical exercise with 8-foot minimum ceiling height, non-slip flooring, adequate ventilation, and storage for exercise equipment. Acceptance criteria: Unobstructed rectangular space minimum 8'x12', rubber or composite flooring, ventilation rate 6 air changes per hour, temperature control 60-75°F, wall-mounted equipment storage, full-spectrum lighting minimum 50 foot-candles.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing ceiling height, flooring specifications, environmental controls, equipment storage, and lighting requirements for safe exercise activities.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall provide a minimum of 100 square feet of space for eating.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall provide a minimum of 100 square feet of dining space with seating for 6 persons, adequate lighting, and proximity to kitchen facilities. Acceptance criteria: Minimum 15 square feet per person, table seating for 6, chairs with back support, task lighting minimum 30 foot-candles, easy-clean surfaces, temperature control 65-75°F, within 20 feet of food preparation area.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing seating capacity, furniture requirements, lighting specifications, proximity to kitchen, and environmental conditions for comfortable dining.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall include at least one table and five chairs.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The facility shall include at least one dining table (minimum 36"x60") and five chairs suitable for daily meals and work activities. Acceptance criteria: Table height 28-30 inches, scratch and stain resistant surface, chairs with back support rated for 250 lbs, stackable or foldable for space efficiency, materials suitable for -40°F to 80°F temperature range.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing furniture dimensions, weight capacity, materials specifications, storage efficiency, and environmental durability requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The refrigeration system shall provide at least 48 cubic feet of refrigeration space.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The refrigeration system shall provide at least 48 cubic feet of refrigeration space maintaining temperature between 32°F and 40°F with ±2°F accuracy. Acceptance criteria: ENERGY STAR certified, automatic defrost, temperature monitoring and alarms, backup power capability for 24 hours, adjustable shelving, door locks, maximum 45 dB noise level.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing temperature specifications, accuracy requirements, energy efficiency standards, monitoring capabilities, and backup power requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The freezer system shall provide at least 19.5 cubic feet of freezer space.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The freezer system shall provide at least 19.5 cubic feet of freezer space maintaining temperature between -10°F and 0°F with ±2°F accuracy. Acceptance criteria: ENERGY STAR certified, manual defrost capability, temperature monitoring and alarms, backup power capability for 24 hours, organized storage compartments, door locks, maximum 45 dB noise level.
